Text.string: Timber! I mean, hey! Heh, sorry—force of habit.
I smell ya.
Oh, hey!
Vault Hunter!
Here comes a Hunter.
Swamp's a'bloomin'—that means good day!
Daytime's for drinking.
Swamp's a crawling—that means good night!
Nightime's for drinking.
Bet you never woulda guessed it, but I'm a lumberjack.
That sensual wood grain on a Jakobs—THAT'S why it only takes one shot.
Eden-6 is in the mud, but we'll pull ourselves out. We always do.
You'd think choppin' wood would prepare me for choppin' necks, but I keep asking myself how many bandit necks could my chopping axe chop, and the answer is always RUN!
Have you seen my axe? It's a nice axe. Real shapely. If I could marry my axe, I would. But we'd probably split sooner or later.
Swamp folk are some of the best musicians in the galaxy. That's a true fact for ya, friend.
I'm a lumberjack, (grimly) and I'm not okay at all.
I fight when I have to, but I'd really rather not.
Some call me a coward. But like I always say... okay, okay, I actually am a coward. Don't tell nobody.
Wish I could be tough like you. But cowardice is in my blood. That's my excuse and I'm sticking to it.
You'll uh, protect us, right?
These big beefy arms were made for choppin' wood, not fightin'.
You ever whittle? Whittlin's a good time.
Until the bandits came, Eden-6 used to be a nice place... sorta. For a swamp... gonna trail off now...
I miss lumberjackin'. Business ain't exactly been boomin' since them COV moved in.
Ain't nothin' to chop down on this ship. That's a shame.
What's a lumberjack like me supposed to do on a damn space ship? I shoulda thought of this ahead of time.
You think Marcus sells axes?
It's nice to be offa' Eden-6 for a change, if I'm bein' real honest.
Maybe Sanctuary can take me to exciting new woods, so I can chop down trees there. A man can dream...
[yawns]
[yawns] I could sleep like a log.
[yawns]
[yawns]
[yawns]
[yawns]
Bye-bye, friend!
So long, Vault Hunter!
As the lumberjack said to the tree: next time, I'm coming for you!
Bye! Come back soon, unless yer dead!
And I'm alone again...
Have a good 'un!
Smell you later!
Stay outta the mud!
Don't get eaten, now!
Bye now!
I'm lonely. There, I said it.
Gotta get back to work one of these days.
Am I doing okay?
Man, I am bored! Someone DO SOMETHING!
What's the point of life anyway? Oh yeah, right... right...
I'm so alone! Someone give me a hug! Any takers?
Lumberjack for sale! You got wood, I'M the solution.
Aw, damn. I got a splinter.
I could really go for some chips.
Scoping out places to hide... just in case.
Gonna whittle me a little wooden jabber. Good luck charm in these dark times.
Ahhh, I love the smell of sawdust in the morning. Nothing like it.
MUD PARTY! Anyone? No? Kay... more for me...
[humming] I'm shipping off to brighter shores! Promethea, here I come!
Was someone calling me? Am I hearing things? Nevermind...
Lumberjackin'!
I got wood!
Trees, ya feel me?
Get it! Hahaha!
I'm gonna build a treehouse!
I just had my first coffee and WHOO!
A country boy can turn the tide!
You folk talk real purty!
Way to kick some axe! [chuckle]
[burp] Anybody got a mint?
[burp] Do not have the guac, people.
[burp] Don't recall eatin' jabber...
[waves excitedly] This here's my axin' hand.
[waves excitedly] Can I “axe” you a question? Sorry.
[waves excitedly] I'm higher than the treetops!
[waves excitedly] Practicin' my greetin's.
[waves excitedly] Social interaction!
[waves excitedly] Gettin' real into gestures lately.
